obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4555  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2 and Table 3: Active neonatal MSNs from GlyRα2KO mice (P6-7) have slower rates of spontaneous firing and altered properties of evoked action potentials.\n\nTo explain the decreased spontaneous firing frequency and accommodation current in GlyRα2KOs, an individual AP analysis was performed (Figure 2G). Both the amplitude and duration of APs in spontaneously active GlyRα2KO cells were severely affected. In GlyRα2KO DS MSNs, the AP half-width is higher (Figure 2H, 3.20 ± 0.43 ms) as compared to WT DS MSNs (2.05 ± 0.08 ms; p < 0.05). This was accompanied by significant changes in the rise and decay rates (Table 3). The amplitude of the APS differed significantly when comparing \"active\" KO and WT cells (Figure 2I).\n\nFigure 4-5: Functional glutamatergic innervation of MSNs is decreased in GlyRα2KO mice but not the number of glutamatergic synaptic contacts on MSNs.\n\nFigure 6: AMPA/NMDA ratio, but not paired-pulse facilitation is reduced in MSNs of adult GlyRα2KO mice.. Experimental description: C57Bl/6 (both genders) and GlyR α2 subunit knockout mice (WTs and GlyRα2KOs, males) of specific ages were used in the study. GlyRα2KOs were initially generated in the laboratory of Prof. Harvey and Prof. T. N. Dear by deletion of the exon 7 of Glra2. GlyRα2KOs were fully back-crossed to C57Bl/6 background and genotyped as described previously (Avila et al., 2013a; D'Angelo et al., 1995)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4555" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

